data.description: Listed by Pam Marion - Call 580-581-7870 for more details. Pam & Barry's Team RE/MAX Professionals sold 517 Properties in 2022 and have been the #1 Choice in Real Estate in SWOK for over 20 Years! This one-of-a-kind home is just a block away from Comanche County Memorial Hospital and Cameron University and allows easy access to shopping, dining, and entertainment. Located on a 1.12-acre tree lined lot that creates a park-like, private atmosphere right in the heart of Lawton.             The bright and spacious open concept floor plan is perfect for entertaining and offers granite countertops throughout and hardwood floors. The kitchen has original custom metal cabinets with lazy susans and pull-out shelves for pots and pans and a large island/breakfast bar with seating for 5.  The Family room/Kitchen showcases approx. 13-foot vaulted ceilings, and the front of the room has wall to wall windows with custom plantation shutters that overlook the front yard, pool area and driveway. A 400 Sq. Ft. formal dining room offers wood parquet floors, vaulted ceilings, down lights and an antique chandelier, as well as are wall to wall windows and French doors with access to the backyard deck. Adjacent to the formal dining room is a large custom wall of bookshelves to create your own home library.   A sitting room/den/office with vaulted ceiling, hardwood floors, stained glass windows and rock wall gas log fireplace leads to a spacious main bedroom with a private bath. The main bathroom has dual sinks, custom built cabinets galore and a whirlpool tub. Other highlights are dual walk-in closets with built in shoe shelving, vanity and 6 closets worth of hanging space in multiple areas. A cedar-lined sunroom with vaulted ceiling offers tons of windows, 2 skylights, 4 stained glass windows and granite countertops with access to the master bedroom. Also, on this level are two spacious guest bedrooms with tons of windows, vaulted ceilings, custom built-in cabinets with lighted vanities and bookshelves and walk-in closets with built-in shelves. The large, updated bathroom off of the hallway has two sinks, custom cabinets, granite countertops, a walk-in shower and bathtub.   On the lower level a rock wall foyer welcomes you and leads to the approx. 1000 sq. ft. tiled great room with surround sound, huge stone fireplace with gas logs, built in custom lighted cabinets with tons of storage and a recessed area to mount a big screen television.  French doors open to the approx. 46' x 20' pool, hot tub, and surrounding area.  Also, located on that level is a bedroom with custom cabinets, built in vanity, plantation shutters and hardwood floors. Plus, 3/4 bath with walk-in shower, built in linen cabinets and granite countertops plus a kitchenette/with sink/wet bar and a space for a refrigerator, dishwasher and ice maker or trash compactor.  This would make for a great guest house, rental, or mother in law suite.
